The paper deals with algorithms for processing data streams, which is a common topic in the computer science subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of finding heavy-hitters is a well-studied problem in the database literature, which falls under the subfield of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses event detection, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses cache-efficient algorithms, which is a topic in the subfield of parallel and distributed computing (cs.CC).
